-- E14 / EMITTER-GAPS #14 (non-Int literal switch): a String-literal match head.
-- The match column is all-String-literal, so the decision tree lowers to an
-- emitLitChain over `HLit (LString _)` heads — each compares the scrutinee cell
-- against a materialized literal cell via the @mdk_string_eq runtime helper
-- (tagged-Bool result, branch on `icmp eq i64 r, 3`).  The first arm ("let")
-- must NOT match and fall through to the second ("if"), proving the chain order.
main = match "if"
  "let" => 1
  "if" => 2
  _ => 0
